\begin_layout Standard
This methodological diversity highlights a central feature of continuous optimization:
 no single search mechanism is uniformly reliable across all problem classes,
 and practical performance depends strongly on how exploration,
 exploitation,
 adaptation,
 and population diversity are coordinated.
 As a result,
 contemporary research has increasingly emphasized robust search behavior,
 parameter control,
 and strategy adaptation rather than purely static algorithmic designs 
