\begin_layout Standard
At initialization,
 the method evaluates the initial population,
 constructs the archive,
 and identifies the initial incumbent.
 It also initializes a stagnation monitor through a reference best value 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{\mathrm{prev}}$
\end_inset

 and a non-improvement counter 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

.
 The branch scheduler is configured for 
\begin_inset Formula $h=2$
\end_inset

 competing branches,
 corresponding to ARQ and IDE.
 A baseline branch credit 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{0}$
\end_inset

 is assigned to each branch,
 the reset threshold is set to 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta=1/(5h)$
\end_inset

,
 the initial active credits satisfy 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{i}=n_{0}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1,2$
\end_inset

,
 the cumulative credit-memory terms satisfy 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{i}=0$
\end_inset

,
 and the reset counter is initialized as 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\mathrm{rst}}=0$
\end_inset

.
 In addition,
 a bootstrap counter 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 is used to enforce the ARQ branch during the first scheduled iterations.
 To maintain a common notion of search progress across the two branches,
 the algorithm uses the evaluation-based progress ratio.
 The value 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta=1/(5h)$
\end_inset

 was selected to ensure that a reset is triggered before any branch is reduced to near-zero selection probability,
 while remaining tolerant enough to allow meaningful credit differentiation between branches.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $h=2$
\end_inset

,
 this yields 
\begin_inset Formula $δ=0.1$
\end_inset

,
 meaning a reset occurs when one branch holds less than ten percent of the total selection probability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pi=\frac{e}{T_{\mathrm{eval}}},
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $e$
\end_inset

 denotes the number of consumed function evaluations and 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{\mathrm{eval}}$
\end_inset

 denotes the total evaluation budget.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At the beginning of each iteration,
 the archive is first trimmed so that its capacity does not exceed
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
