\[
\lfloor\alpha_{A}N\rfloor,
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{A}$
\end_inset

 is the archive-size coefficient.
 The controller then determines which branch will be executed.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $b>0$
\end_inset

,
 the ARQ branch is selected deterministically and the bootstrap counter is decreased by one.
 This is the only stage in which ARQ has strict priority.
 After the bootstrap stage has ended,
 neither ARQ nor IDE has permanent priority,
 instead,
 both branches compete under the same credit-based scheduler.
\end_layout

