\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the selected branch is IDE,
 the method applies a progress-dependent differential update with branch-specific memories for mutation and crossover control.
 To preserve notation consistency with the rest of the manuscript,
 the IDE-side behavior is also expressed through the same global progress ratio 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

.
 The branch first defines the progress-sensitive elite-pressure term
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\varepsilon_{\mathrm{IDE}}(\pi)=0.1+0.9\cdot10^{5(\pi-1)}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This quantity determines the size of the elite-guided pool,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
H(\pi)=\max\{2,\mathrm{round}(\varepsilon_{\mathrm{IDE}}(\pi)N)\}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Accordingly,
 the donor construction follows a progress-dependent mixed strategy.
 In its guidance-oriented regime,
 the branch uses
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{i}=x_{o}+F_{i}(x_{r_{1}}-x_{o})+F_{i}(x_{r_{2}}-x_{r_{3}}),
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{r_{1}}$
\end_inset

 is selected either from the elite pool of size 
\begin_inset Formula $H(\pi)$
\end_inset

 or from a standard random index.
 In the later current-based regime,
 it may instead use
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{i}=x_{i}+F_{i}(x_{r_{1}}-x_{o})+F_{i}(x_{r_{2}}-x_{r_{3}}).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The trial vector is then generated by the same binomial crossover form as above,
 but with branch-specific crossover memory 
\begin_inset Formula $CR_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 After evaluation,
 the IDE branch applies greedy one-to-one replacement.
 Denoting the offspring by 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{i}$
\end_inset

,
 replacement occurs when
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f(u_{i})\leq f(x_{i}),
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
or,
 in the strict variant,
 when 
\begin_inset Formula $f(u_{i})<f(x_{i})$
\end_inset

.
 The IDE-side success rate is then
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
SR=\frac{|S|}{N},
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is the set of successful offspring.
 Therefore,
 within ARQ2,
 IDE acts as a complete complementary search routine rather than as a single isolated mutation formula.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After branch execution,
 additional stabilization is applied only when the selected branch is ARQ.
 The first layer is quarantine-based correction.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{3}$
\end_inset

 denote the third quartile of the fitness distribution and let 
\begin_inset Formula $IQR$
\end_inset

 denote the interquartile range.
 Fitness outliers are identified through
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\theta=Q_{3}+\alpha_{Q}\cdot IQR,
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{Q}$
\end_inset

 is the outlier-sensitivity coefficient.
 A fraction 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{Q}$
\end_inset

 of the detected outliers is then relocated around the center of the better half of the population using Gaussian perturbations scaled by 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{Q}$
\end_inset

.
 The second layer is an ARQ-only micro-restart activated when
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s\geq\tau,
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

 is the stagnation threshold.
 In that case,
 the method perturbs the incumbent neighborhood and attempts to replace the worst fraction 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega$
\end_inset

 of the population using Gaussian noise scaled by 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{R}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finally,
 the iteration ends with a second archive-trimming stage,
 followed by the update of the stopping state and the reporting of the current incumbent.
 Consequently,
 the execution order of ARQ2 is:
 archive maintenance,
 bootstrap-or-roulette scheduling,
 optional controller reset,
 execution of the selected branch,
 ARQ-only stabilization when applicable,
 and final bookkeeping.
 This hierarchy also defines the natural order in which the overall flowchart,
 the roulette-based flowchart,
 the IDE flowchart,
 and the three corresponding pseudocodes should appear in the manuscript.
\end_layout

