noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 provide a complementary view by showing how the compared methods behave on average over repeated independent runs.
 In this table,
 the strongest mean-value outcomes are more evenly distributed than in the best-value table,
 with EA4Eig attaining the best mean values on 19 problems,
 JSO on 17,
 and ARQ2 on 15 when ties are counted.
 Even so,
 ARQ2 remains one of the strongest methods in average-case terms and clearly improves upon ARQ on the majority of benchmark problems.
 This observation is important because mean-value performance is generally more informative about practical optimizer reliability than isolated best-case outcomes.
 Consequently,
 the mean-value results suggest that the proposed method is not only capable of producing highly competitive solutions,
 but also able to preserve that competitiveness with substantial consistency across repeated executions.
