 remain coherent and do not suggest abrupt instability or immediate premature stagnation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From a methodological standpoint,
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:convergenceANDcomplexity"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 supports the conclusion that the additional hybridization introduced in ARQ2 does not merely increase internal procedural complexity.
 Instead,
 it appears to improve the way in which search effort is distributed between exploration and refinement,
 even when the dimensional and structural demands of the problem become more pronounced.
 The dominant computational burden remains associated with repeated objective-function evaluations,
 as is typical for population-based metaheuristics,
 while the internal control mechanisms of ARQ2 contribute to a more effective use of that evaluation budget over time.
 In this sense,
 the proposed method exhibits a favorable empirical balance between convergence efficiency,
 robustness,
 and practical computational demand.
\end_layout

